    • Class net.rem.regression.RMAbstract extends net.hudup.core.alg.ExecutableAlgAbstract implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • coeffs

          java.util.List<E> coeffs
          Regression coefficient.

        • xIndices

          java.util.List<E> xIndices
          Indices for X data, including -1 such as (-1, 0 or #x1, 1 or log(#x1), ..., n-1 or xn). So x1 begins with index 1. Note, every element of xIndices is an array of objects. In current implementation, only the first object in such array is used, which can be index (the index -1 points to 1 value, not point to profile) or expression.

        • zIndices

          java.util.List<E> zIndices
          Indices for Z data, including -1 such as (-1, z). So z has index 1. Note, every element of zIndices is an array of objects. In current implementation, only the first object in such array is used, which can be index (the index -1 points to 1 value, not point to profile) or expression. However, zIndices has 2 elements.

        • attList

          net.hudup.core.data.AttributeList attList
          Attribute list for all variables: all X, Y, and z. This variable is also used as the indicator of successful learning.

    • Class net.rem.regression.em.REMImpl extends REMAbstract implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • data

          LargeStatistics data
          Internal data is the original data for learning. It can have missing values.

        • xIndices

          java.util.List<E> xIndices
          Indices for X data. Each element of xIndixes is an index which is an array of objects. In current implementation, only the first object of the array is used. Such first object can be number, variable name (field name), or mathematical expression. If it is a number called number index, the 0 index always points to 1 and the 1 index points the first field (index 0) of profile. In other words, number index starts with 1 when users specify.

        • zIndices

          java.util.List<E> zIndices
          Indices for Z data. Each element of zIndices is an index which is an array of objects. Note, xIndices has only two indices. In current implementation, only the first object of the array is used. Such first object can be number, variable name (field name), or mathematical expression. If it is a number called number index, the 0 index always points to 1 and the 1 index points the first field (index 0) of profile. In other words, number index starts with 1 when users specify.

        • attList

          net.hudup.core.data.AttributeList attList
          Attribute list for all variables: all X, Y, and z. This variable is also used as the indicator of successful learning (not null).
